org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.driver.js.vf2js

Class JSVF2JSConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.config.Configuration
      • org.apache.flex.compiler.clients.JSConfiguration
        • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.driver.js.goog.JSGoogConfiguration
          • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.driver.js.vf2js.JSVF2JSConfiguration

  • public class JSVF2JSConfiguration
extends JSGoogConfiguration
    The JSVF2JSConfiguration class holds all compiler arguments needed for compiling ActionScript to JavaScript the 'goog' way.

    Specific flags are implemented here for the configuration to be loaded by the configure() method of MXMLJSC.

    This class inherits all compiler arguments from the MXMLC compiler.

    Author:
    Erik de Bruin
